Key technical specifications include:
Control Architecture: The project integrates a Raspberry Pi for high-level control and an Arduino for real-time motor management, enabling precise movement and coordination.
Actuation: Stepper motors drive the gantry system, ensuring accurate positioning and consistent paint application across surfaces.
Spray Mechanism: A calibrated spray nozzle optimizes paint distribution, allowing for uniform coverage while minimizing overspray.
Edge Detection: Implemented using computer vision algorithms, the edge detection system identifies obstacles in the painting area, preventing unwanted paint application and enhancing operational efficiency.
This project exemplifies our expertise in mechatronics, embedded systems, and automation, demonstrating how emerging technologies can be applied to solve practical challenges in everyday tasks. The Gantry Paint Pro not only bridges theoretical knowledge with hands-on experience but also prepares us for future endeavors in engineering and technology.
